tweet: If you’re traveling this holiday season, the @511PAStatewide “Check My Route” feature allows you to see any travel alerts & snow plow updates along a specific route when you enter “start” & “end” points. Covers state roads & PA Turnpike.  http://www.511pa.com/default.aspx

There are 4 @PADMVA programs accepting tax-deductible donations this holiday season to help veterans, active military & their families. You can find information on programs & how to donate online or by mail here:
 https://donate.dmva.pa.gov/

Pennsylvanians seeking substance use disorder treatment for themselves or others can find local treatment options & related services through the Drug and Alcohol Referral Tool (DART). Includes resources for homelessness, transportation to treatment & more.  https://www.humanservices.state.pa.us/Dart

High schools have until Dec. 31 to submit ideas for the @PennDOTNews Innovation Challenge, which this year looks for ways to get drivers to slow down in work zones. Winning teams will be picked regionally, then statewide. https://www.penndot.gov/about-us/PennDOT2020/Pages/Innovations-Challenge.aspx …

The Property Tax/Rent Rebate Program deadline to apply for a rebate on property taxes or rent paid in 2017 is Dec. 31. For income-eligible residents 65 & older, widow/widowers 50 & up, & people with disabilities 18 & up. Applications & rebate tracker here: https://www.revenue.pa.gov/GeneralTaxInformation/PropertyTaxRentRebateProgram/Pages/default.aspx …

The PA State Archives & @PHMC are accepting applications for the 2019 Scholars in Residence Program. Supports up to 4 weeks of full-time research in the manuscript & state record collections maintained by the State Archives. Deadline to apply is Feb. 15. https://www.phmc.pa.gov/Archives/News-Programs/Pages/Scholars-in-Residence-.aspx …

A free @NAIC_News locator service connecting consumers w/ lost life insurance policies/annuities matched 1,546 PA beneficiaries w/ $12.8 million in benefits since 2016. Passage of Act 48 of 2018 made PA insurance co. participation mandatory. Search here:  https://eapps.naic.org/life-policy-locator/#/welcome …

PA hunters can again help feed the hungry via Hunters Sharing the Harvest @ShareDeerPA. Each year, the program provides about 200,000 meals across PA. No charge for processing donated venison at participating sites, which you can find here:  https://sharedeer.org/
